showed.text: Theorem 3.1 Let $G=(V,E)$ be a graph with treewidth at most $k$ and maximum degree at most $d$. Then the domino treewidth of $G$ is at most $(9k+7)d(d+1)-1$.
Lemma 4.3 For all $d \ge 5$, $k \ge 2$, $k$ even, there exists a graph $G$ with treewidth at most $k$, maximum degree at most $d$, and domino treewidth at least $\frac{1}{12} kd-2$.
